text:
Upon learning that Elusia invaded 
Firene Castle, the Divine Dragon's 
army hastens to Queen Ève.

Having regained Firene Castle, the 
party heads to a shrine housing 
the Ring of the Dawn Maiden.

The party attempts to cross the 
border to obtain the ring entrusted 
to the Kingdom of Brodia.

After rebuffing an Elusian attack, 
the Divine Dragon's army reaches 
their destination: Brodia Castle.

The Divine Dragon's army and King 
Morion head to Elusia's border to 
answer King Hyacinth's challenge.

The Divine Dragon's army rushes 
to Destinea Cathedral to rescue 
King Morion.

Their rings lost to Veyle, the party 
heads to the Queendom of Solm to 
regain their footing.

The Divine Dragon's army travels 
to an oasis in search of Timerra 
and the Ring of the Radiant Hero.

Receiving word of Hortensia's 
attack, the Divine Dragon's army 
hastens back to Solm Palace.

Victorious at Solm Palace, the 
party seeks the Ring of the Crux 
of Fate at the Northern Fortress.

While planning their next move 
after getting a new ring, the Divine 
Dragon's army receives a report.

Chasing Elusian warships heading 
to Firene, the Divine Dragon's army 
arrives at Florra Port.

Having learned the truth about 
Veyle, the party heads to Elusia, 
where the Fell Dragon waits.

The Divine Dragon's army arrives 
at a lively Elusian port after 
fending off attackers at sea.

After recovering two rings from 
Marni and Mauvier, the party 
reaches Elusia Castle at last.

Having learned a harsh truth from 
Griss, the party pursues the Fell 
Dragon to Lythos Castle.

Seeking to break the barrier in the 
sky above Elyos, the party hunts 
down a Fell Dragon Shard.

Armed with a powerful artifact 
from Zephia, the party heads to a 
lake in pursuit of a sunken shard.

After meeting the Divine Dragon's 
past self, only one shard remains. 
But a dark surprise lies in wait...

Can the Divine's Dragon army save 
the residents of a peaceful village 
when the Corrupted attack?

In a bandit stronghold, a little thief 
is looking for treasure.
